Policies:
(a) Priority alone. Ideal upper bound. [db-a.cpp]
(b) Unmanaged co-location: all BE batches target P's CC. [db-b.cpp]
(c) Random BE migration: each batch targets a random CC; BE_RANDOM_CC0_PCT
    biases how often it collides with P's CC (25 = uniform, 100 = b). [db-c.cpp]
(d) Random BE throttling: BE keeps targeting P's CC but skips
    BE_THROTTLE_PCT% of batches (removes work instead of moving it). [db-d.cpp]
(e) PingPoint-guided migration: every batch targets a uniform random
    non-P CC; P's CC sees no BE traffic. [db-e.cpp]
